{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2cb168b0-d9b5-46ba-ba31-6f4ab1ae112a","content":"The project directory doesn't exist yet, but here's what you need to configure in your `.csproj` to publish as a dotnet tool:\n\n### Required `.csproj` properties\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n  <PackAsTool>true</PackAsTool>\n  <ToolCommandName>my-mcp-server</ToolCommandName>\n\n  <!-- NuGet metadata -->\n  <PackageId>MyMcpServer</PackageId>\n  <Version>1.0.0</Version>\n  <Authors>YourName</Authors>\n  <Description>An MCP server for ...</Description>\n  <PackageReadmeFile>README.md</PackageReadmeFile>\n  <PackageLicenseExpression>MIT</PackageLicenseExpression>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n### Key points\n\n- **`PackAsTool`** — makes `dotnet pack` produce a tool package\n- **`ToolCommandName`** — the CLI command users run (e.g., `my-mcp-server`)\n- **`OutputType` must be `Exe`** — tools must be executable\n\n### Publish workflow\n\n```bash\n# Pack\ndotnet pack -c Release\n\n# Push to NuGet.org (get API key from nuget.org/account/apikeys)\ndotnet nuget push bin/Release/MyMcpServer.1.0.0.nupkg \\\n  --api-key YOUR_API_KEY \\\n  --source https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json\n```\n\n### Users install & run with\n\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g MyMcpServer\nmy-mcp-server  # runs via stdio\n```\n\nWould you like me to create or update the actual `.csproj` file?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"97af2394-4487-4211-a3fd-3dc2ea512873","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The directory doesn't exist yet. The user is asking what they need to configure, not asking me to do it. Let me give them guidance on what's needed to publish a C# MCP server as a dotnet tool to NuGet.org.","outputTokens":504,"requestId":"3C09:1C1C65:1EE4929:22D2D21:69E81DB3"},"id":"9d354029-5da7-4435-9835-43fca8567b04","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:00:45.227Z","parentId":"8e4c982a-cf94-4b11-b0f8-89d8c30e4656"}
